# TinyHub Project Structure & Codebase Map

This document describes the directory layout, files, and core functions of the TinyHub project. External AI agents should use this map to understand which files to review and edit.

---

## Directory Overview

```
gitme/
├── app.py                      # Flask local development server
├── requirements.txt            # Python dependencies specification
├── check_deploy.js             # Pre-deployment environment configuration checker
├── firebase.json               # Firebase deployment configuration
├── firestore.rules             # Database security rules
├── storage.rules               # Cloud Storage security rules
├── public/                     # Static frontend files (Single source of truth)
│   ├── index.html              # Project upload portal
│   ├── browser.html            # Repository / file browser UI
│   ├── app.js                  # Frontend application logic
│   └── style.css               # Styling and typography
├── functions/                  # Production Firebase Cloud Functions
│   └── index.js                # Serverless Express API & routes
├── tests/                      # Testing suite
│   └── test_app.py             # Unit tests for local Flask server
└── data/                       # Local Git repository storage (created at runtime)
```

