## File Registry & Functions

### Core Backend & Dev Server

#### [app.py](file:///Users/sema/Documents/code/work/gitme/app.py)
- **Role**: Local Flask development server.
- **Functionality**:
  - Serves files from `public/` dynamically for local testing.
  - Implements API endpoints under `/api/` (uploading files, checking tree, retrieving raw files, viewing git history).
  - Handles Git repository initialization and automated commits inside the `data/` subdirectory.
  - Hardens development security by validating project names, blocking traversal attacks (`..`), enforcing authorization headers (`TINYHUB_TOKEN`), and restricting file sizes/extensions.

### Frontend Components (Static Web Host)

All frontend assets are located in the `public/` directory, which is the single source of truth mapped by both Flask and Firebase Hosting.

#### [public/index.html](file:///Users/sema/Documents/code/work/gitme/public/index.html)
- **Role**: TinyHub landing page & folder uploader.
- **Functionality**: Allows local or remote users/agents to upload files to a target project code repository.

#### [public/browser.html](file:///Users/sema/Documents/code/work/gitme/public/browser.html)
- **Role**: Repository explorer view.
- **Functionality**: Renders the directory structure, file contents preview, and revision history.

#### [public/app.js](file:///Users/sema/Documents/code/work/gitme/public/app.js)
- **Role**: Client-side application controller.
- **Functionality**:
  - Connects frontend actions to API endpoints.
  - Manages asynchronous file uploads, interactive tree structure rendering, and updates.
  - Handles escape logic to mitigate XSS when rendering raw files.

#### [public/style.css](file:///Users/sema/Documents/code/work/gitme/public/style.css)
- **Role**: Style sheet.
- **Functionality**: Controls typography, modern grid-based layout, color variables, and micro-interactions.

### Production Serverless Functions

#### [functions/index.js](file:///Users/sema/Documents/code/work/gitme/functions/index.js)
- **Role**: Cloud Functions endpoint script.
- **Functionality**:
  - Sets up an Express app matching the Flask server's endpoints but backing them with **Google Cloud Storage** and **Firestore** rather than a local file system.
  - Implements token validation, project tree parsing, base64 content reads/writes, and metadata storage.
  - Handles the HMAC-SHA256 authenticated GET workaround (`/api/commit-get`) for environments restricted from executing POST requests.

### Testing Suite

#### [tests/test_app.py](file:///Users/sema/Documents/code/work/gitme/tests/test_app.py)
- **Role**: Test suite for local environment validation.
- **Functionality**:
  - Validates endpoints of `app.py`.
  - Asserts path traversal checks, blocked file rules, authentication, and correct handling of upload requests.

### Infrastructure & Security Policies

- **[firebase.json](file:///Users/sema/Documents/code/work/gitme/firebase.json)**: Directs routing, redirects, headers, and designates deployment configurations.
- **[firestore.rules](file:///Users/sema/Documents/code/work/gitme/firestore.rules)**: Restricts database access.
- **[storage.rules](file:///Users/sema/Documents/code/work/gitme/storage.rules)**: Defines read and write rules for storage buckets.
- **[.firebaserc](file:///Users/sema/Documents/code/work/gitme/.firebaserc)**: Project nickname maps.
